article.description: Keith Braxton had 21 points as St. Francis (Pa.) easily defeated Fairleigh Dickinson 87-62 on Thursday night.
article.headline: St. Francis (Pa.) routs Fairleigh Dickinson 87-62
article.story: TEANECK, N.J. -- Keith Braxton had 21 points as St. Francis (Pa.) easily defeated Fairleigh Dickinson 87-62 on Thursday night. Braxton made 4 of 6 3-pointers. He added eight rebounds. Jamaal King had 15 points for St. Francis (Pa.) (13-11, 9-4 Northeast Conference), which earned its sixth straight victory. Isaiah Blackmon added 14 points. Andre Wolford had 11 points for the visitors. Mike Holloway Jr. scored a season-high 22 points for the Knights (12-13, 7-6). Kaleb Bishop added four blocks. The Red Flash leveled the season series against the Knights with the win. Fairleigh Dickinson defeated St. Francis (Pa.) 79-61 on Jan. 5. St. Francis (Pa.) plays Robert Morris at home on Saturday. Fairleigh Dickinson plays Bryant at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
